briefTitle: Study to Evaluate Efficacy, Safety and Immunogenicity of GSK Biologicals' Herpes Zoster (HZ) Vaccine GSK1437173A in Adults Aged 50 Years and Older

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Confirmed Herpes Zoster (HZ) Cases
outcomeMeasures.description: Confirmed HZ cases during the study were assessed in the Modified Total Vaccinated Cohort (mTVc)

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Any Episodes of Post-Herpetic Neuralgia (PHN)
outcomeMeasures.description: The incidence of PHN was calculated using the modified total vaccinated chort.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With a Reduction of Duration of Severe 'Worst' HZ-associated Pain
outcomeMeasures.description: Severe 'worst' pain was defined as HZ-associated pain rated as 3 or above on the 'worst pain' Zoster Brief Pain Inventory (ZBPI) questionnaire. The outcome assessed the duration of severe 'worst' HZ-associated pain following the onset of a confirmed HZ rash over the entire pain reporting period as measured by the ZBPI in subjects with confirmed HZ. This analysis involved any subject reporting clinically significant pain (i.e. pain with a score of 3 or more on a 0-10 point scale) at any time during the study.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Confirmed HZ Episode Related Mortality
outcomeMeasures.description: The analysis focused on the number of subjects who died due to HZ

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With HZ Related Complications
outcomeMeasures.description: The analysis focused on the incidence of HZ complications in subjects with confirmed HZ

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Confirmed HZ Episode Related Hospitalizations
outcomeMeasures.description: The analysis focused on confirmed HZ episode related hospitalizations.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With a Confirmed HZ Episode Having a Reduction of Duration of Pain Medication Associated With HZ
outcomeMeasures.description: The analysis focused on patients who experienced a reduction in duration of pain medication administered for HZ in subjects with confirmed HZ.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With a Confirmed HZ Episode Taking Pain Medication Associated With HZ
outcomeMeasures.description: The analysis focused on subjects taking pain medication due to HZ

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Days With Severe 'Worst' HZ-associated Pain.
outcomeMeasures.description: Severe 'worst' pain was defined as HZ-associated pain rated as 3 or above on the 'worst pain' ZBPI questionnaire. This Outcome Measure was only assessed participants with confirmed HZ. This analysis involved any subject reporting ZBPI clinically significant pain (i.e. pain with a score of 3 or more on a 0-10 point scale) at any time during the study.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Confirmed HZ Episode Related Mortality and Hospitalizations
outcomeMeasures.description: The analysis focused on confirmed HZ episode related hospitalizations and deaths.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With HZ Related Complications, by Complication Type
outcomeMeasures.description: Complication types included HZ vasculitis, Disseminated Disease, Ophtalmic Disease, Neurologic Disease, Visceral Disease and Stroke. This Outcome Measure was only assessed participants with confirmed HZ.

outcomeMeasures.title: Distribution of Pain Medication Associated With HZ
outcomeMeasures.description: The distribution of pain medication included 1 to 3 or more separate medications. This Outcome Measure was only assessed on participants with confirmed HZ.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Days of Pain Medication Associated With HZ
outcomeMeasures.description: The analysis was performed on subjects with a confirmed HZ episode

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Any and Grade 3 Solicited Local Symptoms
outcomeMeasures.description: Assessed solicited local symptoms were pain, redness and swelling. Any = occurrence of the symptom regardless of intensity grade. Grade 3 pain = Significant pain at rest that prevented normal activity. Grade 3 redness/swelling = redness/swelling spreading beyond 100 millimeters (mm) of injection site. Relationship analysis was not performed.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Any, Grade 3 and Related Solicited General Symptoms
outcomeMeasures.description: Assessed solicited general symptoms were fatigue, GI (gastrointestinal) symptoms (included nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea and/or abdominal pain), fever \[defined as oral, axillary, rectal or tympanic temperature equal to or above 37.5 degrees Celsius (°C)\], headache, myalgia, shivering and sweating. Any = occurrence of the symptom regardless of intensity grade. Grade 3 symptom = symptom that prevented normal activity. Grade 3 fever = temperature\> 39.0 °C. Related = symptom assessed by the investigator as related to the vaccination.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Any and Grade 3 Symptoms (Solicited and Unsolicited)
outcomeMeasures.description: Number of subjects with any and grade 3 solicited and unsolicited symptoms were tabulated

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Any and Related Potential Immune Mediated Diseases (pIMDs)
outcomeMeasures.description: Occurrence and relationship to vaccination of any potential immune-mediated diseases (pIMDs) in all subjects

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With AEs With Any and Related Medically Attended Visit
outcomeMeasures.description: Occurrence and relationship to vaccination of medically attended visits (defined as hospitalizations, emergency room visits or visits to or from medical personnel), other than routine health care visits in all subjects.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Unsolicited Adverse Events (AEs)
outcomeMeasures.description: Occurrence, intensity and relationship to vaccination of unsolicited AEs, according to the Medical Dictionary for Regulatory Activities (MedDRA) classification in all subjects An unsolicited AE covers any untoward medical occurrence in a clinical investigation subject temporally associated with the use of a medicinal product, whether or not considered related to the medicinal product and reported in addition to those solicited during the clinical study and any solicited symptom with onset outside the specified period of follow-up for solicited symptoms. Any was defined as the occurrence of any unsolicited AE regardless of intensity grade or relation to vaccination. Grade 3 AE = an AE which prevented normal, everyday activities. Related = AE assessed by the investigator as related to the vaccination.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Serious Adverse Events (SAEs)
outcomeMeasures.description: Occurrence and relationship to vaccination of all SAEs in all subjects. Serious adverse events (SAEs) assessed include medical occurrences that result in death, are life threatening, require hospitalization or prolongation of hospitalization or result in disability/incapacity.

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With SAEs Related to Study Participation or to a Concurrent GSK Medication/Vaccine
outcomeMeasures.description: The number of subjects with SAEs related to study participation or to a concurrent GSK medication/vaccine were tabulated

outcomeMeasures.title: Number of Subjects With Fatal SAEs
outcomeMeasures.description: Number of subjects with fatal SAEs during the entire study period were tabulated
